  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Admitted traffic and context events"]
    C2["Identity and relationship references inside those events"]
    C3["Event-time ordering surfaces"]
    C4["Run-scoped correlation"]
    C5["The platform's rules about which source families are allowed in runtime"]
    C6["Entity relationship posture must be pinned from observed data behavior such as joinability, key stability, and late-arrival behavior"]
    C7["The path is not just syntactic projection; it carries enough meaning to support real relationship state"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats entity truth as something it computes and owns, not something it merely receives"]
    L2["The platform is not saying: the schema already tells us what the entity relationships are"]
    L3["It is saying: relationship posture has to be earned from observed data behavior and then projected into current runtime graph"]
    L4["That is why the semantic-hardening work included entity-map candidate hypotheses"]
    L5["This makes the path clearly intentional rather than accidental"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The path is seated across admitted traffic and context topics on the event bus"]
    S2["The RTDL namespace and worker surfaces consume those topics"]
    S3["Entity and graph and feature surfaces are part of the RTDL namespace"]
    S4["Entity and feature state are written into Aurora"]
    S5["The handles registry pins one RTDL consumer group"]
    S6["Commit policy is commit after durable write"]
    S7["The broader repo authority declares managed Flink runtime surfaces for RTDL stream processing, but in this notebook's copied baseline wired view those managed surfaces are retained rather than the primary reader-facing active output path"]
    S8["So the path is concretely realized as event-bus intake plus RTDL worker surfaces plus durable state seating"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform deliberately chose to make entity and relationship projection a first-class RTDL responsibility"]
    Y2["It did not scatter projection work across generic services"]
    Y3["It did not assume relationships from schema alone"]
    Y4["The path is intentionally seated inside the RTDL runtime and store topology rather than hidden inside downstream context builders"]
    Y5["Entity relationship posture must be pinned from observed data behavior rather than schema-only assumptions"]
    Y6["The current path shape is consciously chosen runtime projection design with explicit semantic discipline"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The runtime data contract says live runtime may use only the four allowed oracle output families"]
    X2["Truth-only outputs and future-implying fields are forbidden"]
    X3["The semantic-hardening posture says entity relationship posture must be based on observed data behavior, not schema-only assumptions"]
    X4["The run-process says RTDL projection closure must be real enough to contribute to RTDL catch-up closure"]
    X5["So this path sits under runtime data law, semantic realism law, and RTDL closure law"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately accepts structure and discipline in exchange for cleaner runtime truth"]
    T2["It would be easier to collapse entity logic into downstream context builders"]
    T3["It would be easier to assume schema-level relationships or scatter this work across loosely governed services"]
    T4["The current design rejects that"]
    T5["It chooses one active RTDL runtime posture, explicit runtime-allowed source families, and explicit downstream dependence on projection correctness"]
    T6["That adds discipline and constrains shortcuts, but buys the cleaner claim that entity truth is constructed intentionally inside RTDL"]
    T7["It also means the path inherits stream-runtime constraints such as checkpoint behavior, lag posture, and replay safety"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still ingest traffic, publish to the bus, and draw downstream boxes like context formation, feature readiness, and decisioning"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to where current entity truth comes from"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to how relationship state is formed and what downstream context is anchored on"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to why later decision truth should be trusted"]
    N5["If the entity and graph layer is wrong, entity truth becomes unreliable and every downstream decision is polluted"]
    N6["Without this path, the rest of RTDL starts to look like a decision system built on unowned relationship assumptions"]
    N7["That would weaken A immediately"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Current entity and relationship projection truth for the active run"]
    O2["RTDL now has graph and projection state that downstream context formation can read as authoritative current surface"]
    O3["Distinct graph-oriented status surface exists with graph_version, checkpoint age, and apply state"]
    O4["Owned outcome: downstream-readable projection truth rather than raw events alone"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for building current entity and relationship truth from admitted live data"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>that truth is constructed in a dedicated RTDL projection lane, not left implicit in raw events or schema assumptions"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in the event bus, RTDL runtime surfaces, RTDL consumer group and commit policy, and the durable state stores behind projection truth"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>the path is constrained by runtime-allowed output families, no-future rules, and observed-data entity-mapping posture"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the system knowingly avoids schema-only convenience and keeps projection state as first-class runtime responsibility"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>current graph truth becomes a real, owned runtime surface that later context and decision logic can honestly stand on"]
  end

